1
00:00:55,133 --> 00:00:55,867
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:55,867 --> 00:00:56,701
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:56,701 --> 00:00:57,502
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

4
00:00:57,502 --> 00:00:58,270
(for filming child actors and animals.)

5
00:01:12,197 --> 00:01:12,998
Sir, now.

6
00:01:12,998 --> 00:01:14,366
Hold on. Wait.

7
00:01:22,607 --> 00:01:23,675
Hey.

8
00:01:24,309 --> 00:01:25,811
I told you to wait.

9
00:01:36,822 --> 00:01:39,124
Curry smells good.

10
00:01:41,159 --> 00:01:41,993
What?

11
00:01:44,329 --> 00:01:47,165
Good grief. I told you not to do that.

12
00:01:49,134 --> 00:01:50,669
Where did Myo Jin go?

13
00:01:50,669 --> 00:01:51,870
It's about time to eat.

14
00:01:54,139 --> 00:01:55,774
Did she go fishing with Muljjeong again?

15
00:01:57,876 --> 00:02:00,178
It's always that Muljjeong.

16
00:02:01,813 --> 00:02:04,015
I'll go bring them back, so set out
one more set of spoon and chopsticks.

17
00:02:04,850 --> 00:02:06,818
You really shouldn't be like that.

18
00:02:09,554 --> 00:02:11,456
If you care so much about him,

19
00:02:11,690 --> 00:02:14,092
go eat out with him yourself
and just send our kid home.

20
00:02:14,493 --> 00:02:16,728
Stop letting an outsider
hang around the house.

21
00:02:16,728 --> 00:02:19,097
Outsider?

22
00:02:19,097 --> 00:02:20,665
Are you going to keep saying that?

23
00:02:20,665 --> 00:02:22,501
Is Muljjeongi a stranger to us?

24
00:02:22,934 --> 00:02:24,436
Of course, he's a stranger.

25
00:02:25,404 --> 00:02:27,773
He's not even blind
or missing his arms or legs,

26
00:02:28,507 --> 00:02:31,843
but he still can't earn his keep at
that age, so he's a good-for-nothing bum.

27
00:02:32,077 --> 00:02:33,779
He's a bad influence on our girl too.

28
00:02:34,246 --> 00:02:35,514
Have you already forgotten?

29
00:02:35,847 --> 00:02:37,549
When we first moved here,

30
00:02:37,549 --> 00:02:39,618
who stood up
to the whole neighborhood for us?

31
00:02:40,419 --> 00:02:42,354
From teaching us how to raise seedlings...

32
00:02:42,354 --> 00:02:43,722
to introducing us to clients.

33
00:02:44,356 --> 00:02:47,359
Who do you think
we owe our livelihood to now?

34
00:02:49,194 --> 00:02:50,829
Do you really not remember anymore?

35
00:02:55,934 --> 00:02:57,069
I'm going to bring them back.

36
00:03:03,942 --> 00:03:05,844
I'm so grateful I could cry.

37
00:03:05,844 --> 00:03:08,180
Really.

38
00:03:10,749 --> 00:03:12,851
You're really good at catching fish.

39
00:03:13,418 --> 00:03:14,753
Why can't I do it?

40
00:03:15,020 --> 00:03:16,855
I haven't caught a single one yet.

41
00:03:19,291 --> 00:03:20,559
Myo Jin.

42
00:03:21,660 --> 00:03:24,329
Why can't you catch fish?

43
00:03:24,930 --> 00:03:26,631
You said I keep rushing.

44
00:03:26,898 --> 00:03:28,200
That I don't wait patiently.

45
00:03:30,769 --> 00:03:32,904
Right. If you know what the problem is,

46
00:03:32,904 --> 00:03:34,573
then why do you still think
you can't catch them?

47
00:03:35,173 --> 00:03:36,775
Because fishing is hard.

48
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:38,343
But I can catch other things well.

49
00:03:39,778 --> 00:03:40,612
Really?

50
00:03:42,114 --> 00:03:44,916
Then should we go catch something else?

51
00:03:45,751 --> 00:03:49,087
You said you're good at catching
everything else, so let's see.

52
00:03:54,059 --> 00:03:54,893
Myo Jin.

53
00:03:55,727 --> 00:03:59,197
Whether you're catching fish
or catching a wild boar,

54
00:03:59,197 --> 00:04:01,066
the method is the same.

55
00:04:01,767 --> 00:04:02,667
What is?

56
00:04:02,868 --> 00:04:04,603
The thing you want to catch.

57
00:04:05,537 --> 00:04:06,938
Think like that thing.

58
00:04:07,973 --> 00:04:09,574
When it'll get hungry,

59
00:04:10,342 --> 00:04:11,843
where you should wait,

60
00:04:11,843 --> 00:04:14,413
and what kind of bait to use.

61
00:04:16,348 --> 00:04:17,482
And then?

62
00:04:19,718 --> 00:04:21,420
You set a trap...

63
00:04:21,420 --> 00:04:22,487
and wait.

64
00:04:23,188 --> 00:04:26,191
The bait changes,
but the way you catch it is the same.

65
00:04:27,359 --> 00:04:28,226
Lastly,

66
00:04:29,494 --> 00:04:30,796
there's just one thing
you need to remember.

67
00:04:31,630 --> 00:04:34,266
Don't rush. Take it slow.

68
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:35,867
That's right.

69
00:04:37,402 --> 00:04:39,204
Myo Jin, Muljjeong.

70
00:04:39,504 --> 00:04:40,939
Come on and eat.

71
00:04:41,573 --> 00:04:43,108
Your mom made curry.

72
00:04:43,475 --> 00:04:44,643
Come on, both of you.

73
00:04:45,210 --> 00:04:46,044
- Curry?
- Curry?

74
00:04:46,478 --> 00:04:47,379
Let's go.

75
00:04:53,685 --> 00:04:56,488
(Hunt)

76
00:04:57,589 --> 00:05:01,126
(NFS)

77
00:05:06,732 --> 00:05:10,068
You're pestering me
this early in the morning.

78
00:05:10,068 --> 00:05:11,136
Where's Detective Woo?

79
00:05:11,136 --> 00:05:12,971
He says he has something else
to take care of.

80
00:05:13,805 --> 00:05:16,007
He calls nonstop when he needs something,

81
00:05:16,007 --> 00:05:17,409
then disappears when it's time to show up.

82
00:05:18,343 --> 00:05:19,277
He's unusual.

83
00:05:21,513 --> 00:05:22,581
Did anything turn up?

84
00:05:24,249 --> 00:05:25,684
Not from our team yet.

85
00:05:26,184 --> 00:05:29,354
I went back over
Choi Hee Su's autopsy results first,

86
00:05:29,755 --> 00:05:30,989
and it's definitely homicide.

87
00:05:32,224 --> 00:05:33,558
Anyway, give it a little more time.

88
00:05:34,793 --> 00:05:37,362
Even at a fire scene,

89
00:05:37,729 --> 00:05:39,398
something always turns up.

90
00:05:40,499 --> 00:05:42,667
Now I'm curious who did it.

91
00:05:42,667 --> 00:05:45,604
Cases like this are rare
unless the killer is a real veteran.

92
00:05:47,105 --> 00:05:48,940
Could an ordinary person do it,

93
00:05:49,641 --> 00:05:51,410
if they were smart and meticulous?

94
00:05:52,844 --> 00:05:53,779
It's hard to say.

95
00:05:55,113 --> 00:05:55,947
Then again,

96
00:05:55,947 --> 00:05:57,482
when I get curious these days,

97
00:05:57,482 --> 00:05:59,518
I learn things through social media.

98
00:06:00,018 --> 00:06:01,219
Sometimes that's better.

99
00:06:05,057 --> 00:06:07,559
I heard they found
a woman's footprint at the scene.

100
00:06:07,926 --> 00:06:08,927
A woman's footprint?

101
00:06:11,630 --> 00:06:13,298
What's unusual is that it was barefoot.

102
00:06:13,665 --> 00:06:16,334
Judging by the shape and size,
it's definitely a woman's,

103
00:06:16,735 --> 00:06:18,336
and they said
there was blood mixed in too.

104
00:06:18,670 --> 00:06:19,571
Did you know?

105
00:06:20,272 --> 00:06:21,139
No.

106
00:06:21,573 --> 00:06:24,476
But how could a footprint
from back then be found only now?

107
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:26,745
That doesn't make sense.

108
00:06:26,745 --> 00:06:29,748
Some idiot must've missed evidence
they collected at the time.

109
00:06:30,382 --> 00:06:32,484
That's what happens
when people do their jobs like that.

110
00:06:32,484 --> 00:06:35,087
No wonder they all had to write reports
and got warnings too.

111
00:06:35,721 --> 00:06:38,323
How do you miss evidence
that was properly submitted?

112
00:06:39,291 --> 00:06:40,225
Wait.

113
00:06:40,625 --> 00:06:42,861
The person in charge here said
there was a reason.

114
00:06:43,628 --> 00:06:45,063
Detective Kang, was it?

115
00:06:45,063 --> 00:06:47,733
That guy came here alone to the NFS...

116
00:06:47,733 --> 00:06:49,735
and submitted only that piece
of evidence separately.

117
00:06:49,735 --> 00:06:51,436
Do you know Detective Kang?

118
00:06:51,436 --> 00:06:52,504
I do.

119
00:06:52,504 --> 00:06:54,506
He came here himself? Alone?

120
00:06:54,506 --> 00:06:56,108
He did.

121
00:06:56,108 --> 00:06:58,009
He asked the person in charge here...

122
00:06:58,009 --> 00:07:00,312
if he knew anyone at their station.

123
00:07:00,312 --> 00:07:02,114
When they said no,

124
00:07:02,114 --> 00:07:04,049
Detective Kang said,
"Then that's fine," and handed it over.

125
00:07:05,851 --> 00:07:06,685
Anyway,

126
00:07:07,552 --> 00:07:09,454
since you're here,
go talk to the person in charge.

127
00:07:10,122 --> 00:07:11,356
Yes, thank you.

128
00:07:11,857 --> 00:07:12,791
All right.

129
00:07:16,528 --> 00:07:17,662
Detective Kang did that?

130
00:07:18,096 --> 00:07:20,265
That punk just pulled off another one.

131
00:07:20,932 --> 00:07:22,267
So you confirmed it too, right?

132
00:07:22,267 --> 00:07:23,068
Yes.

133
00:07:23,068 --> 00:07:25,437
I begged them to fax
only that part just now,

134
00:07:25,437 --> 00:07:26,338
so compare it.

135
00:07:26,338 --> 00:07:27,672
Okay. Good work.

136
00:07:38,216 --> 00:07:39,151
Let's see.

137
00:07:39,584 --> 00:07:40,619
(Personal Information)

138
00:07:41,787 --> 00:07:44,356
Height, 166.7cm.

139
00:07:44,356 --> 00:07:46,558
Okay, 165 cm.

140
00:07:46,558 --> 00:07:48,160
Foot size, 240 mm.

141
00:07:48,794 --> 00:07:49,995
Two hundred forty.

142
00:07:52,197 --> 00:07:53,165
Bingo.

143
00:07:54,633 --> 00:07:55,834
Thank you, Detective Kang.

144
00:07:56,702 --> 00:07:57,869
That guy.

145
00:08:10,949 --> 00:08:13,518
(Call, Myo Jin 17 calls)

146
00:08:19,591 --> 00:08:21,960
So the villa accident was a murder...

147
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:23,829
disguised as a fire.

148
00:08:23,829 --> 00:08:26,598
Based on the wound location
and depth pattern,

149
00:08:27,366 --> 00:08:29,568
it was most likely a grudge killing.

150
00:08:36,441 --> 00:08:37,476
I told you clearly...

151
00:08:37,476 --> 00:08:39,511
that Ham Myo Jin is back to normal.

152
00:08:40,011 --> 00:08:42,347
But isn't it terrifying
that she's pretending she isn't?

153
00:08:42,347 --> 00:08:44,282
In her current condition,

154
00:08:44,916 --> 00:08:46,818
her memory could come back at any time.

155
00:08:48,019 --> 00:08:50,122
(Myo Jin)

156
00:08:50,322 --> 00:08:51,156
Myo Jin.

157
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:03,268
Why haven't you been answering?

158
00:09:03,802 --> 00:09:04,803
Where are you right now?

159
00:09:05,203 --> 00:09:06,238
I have something to say.

160
00:09:07,572 --> 00:09:08,407
Okay.

161
00:09:08,774 --> 00:09:11,877
I'll be there soon,

162
00:09:11,877 --> 00:09:12,911
so we'll talk when I get there.

163
00:09:13,412 --> 00:09:15,213
You're at home, right?

164
00:09:15,213 --> 00:09:16,048
No.

165
00:09:17,883 --> 00:09:18,850
Then where are you?

166
00:09:20,152 --> 00:09:21,586
Somewhere you know too.

167
00:10:12,838 --> 00:10:14,373
You still don't know me?

168
00:10:15,540 --> 00:10:16,942
Do you really think...

169
00:10:17,642 --> 00:10:19,244
I'd ask you a favor for free?

170
00:10:19,678 --> 00:10:22,681
Why are you back here
making a fuss and annoying me?

171
00:10:23,081 --> 00:10:25,550
Listen properly first,

172
00:10:25,550 --> 00:10:27,719
then get angry or annoyed.

173
00:10:28,587 --> 00:10:30,122
Honestly, I call it a favor,

174
00:10:30,589 --> 00:10:32,290
but is this really something
I'm doing only for myself?

175
00:10:33,558 --> 00:10:35,360
Then are you okay...

176
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:37,095
with what those two are doing?

177
00:10:37,429 --> 00:10:40,265
You eat expensive food
and really have nothing better to do?

178
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:44,069
Unlike you, I don't care
about other people's business.

179
00:10:44,069 --> 00:10:45,303
Other people?

180
00:10:45,904 --> 00:10:48,240
Right. Sure, they're other people.

181
00:10:48,940 --> 00:10:50,842
Other people who ruined someone's life...

182
00:10:50,842 --> 00:10:52,711
and then lived happily
like nothing happened.

183
00:10:53,045 --> 00:10:54,079
Damn it.

184
00:10:54,613 --> 00:10:56,314
Honestly, the money you got back then...

185
00:10:56,982 --> 00:10:58,917
wouldn't even cover
that family's dog food.

186
00:10:59,518 --> 00:11:01,319
After all those years in prison,

187
00:11:01,987 --> 00:11:03,855
what kind of payment is this?

188
00:11:03,855 --> 00:11:05,323
It makes me mad just thinking about it.

189
00:11:06,124 --> 00:11:08,627
That dog-food money bought me this place.

190
00:11:09,494 --> 00:11:11,329
If it's heaven to me, that's enough.

191
00:11:11,329 --> 00:11:13,799
Anyone listening would think
you're some enlightened monk.

192
00:11:17,069 --> 00:11:19,271
Cut the crap and talk straight.

193
00:11:20,505 --> 00:11:21,673
Why on earth...

194
00:11:22,174 --> 00:11:24,342
are you so desperate to destroy that girl?

195
00:11:28,313 --> 00:11:29,281
Fine.

196
00:11:33,885 --> 00:11:35,487
Today, we put all our cards on the table,

197
00:11:36,154 --> 00:11:37,556
and after that, no more arguments.

198
00:11:37,789 --> 00:11:38,623
Okay?

199
00:11:40,559 --> 00:11:41,960
First, we grab Ham Myo Jin,

200
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:43,895
that cocky little bitch, by the throat,

201
00:11:44,629 --> 00:11:46,965
and use her to shake down
that thief Ryu Jun Ho.

202
00:11:47,566 --> 00:11:48,600
I saw that bastard Ryu Jun Ho...

203
00:11:49,868 --> 00:11:51,970
nurse Ham Myo Jin,

204
00:11:52,170 --> 00:11:54,606
and he was absolutely crazy about her.

205
00:11:54,940 --> 00:11:56,441
Of course.

206
00:11:56,975 --> 00:12:00,312
So in the end, you want to squeeze
money out of Mono Group?

207
00:12:01,313 --> 00:12:02,547
Exactly.

208
00:12:02,547 --> 00:12:04,316
Now you're finally getting it.

209
00:12:04,316 --> 00:12:06,718
Do you think...

210
00:12:06,718 --> 00:12:07,819
he will dance to your threats...

211
00:12:08,286 --> 00:12:09,821
over a girl...

212
00:12:10,589 --> 00:12:13,592
when he's the next head of
a conglomerate worth hundreds of billions?

213
00:12:13,592 --> 00:12:15,260
This is why you're so frustrating.

214
00:12:15,994 --> 00:12:18,030
You really don't know anything.

215
00:12:19,564 --> 00:12:20,732
After Chairman Choi and his daughter...

216
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:23,869
burned to death overnight,

217
00:12:24,636 --> 00:12:27,372
Ham Myo Jin and Ryu Jun Ho are together.
Why do you think that is?

218
00:12:29,341 --> 00:12:30,175
Look at you.

219
00:12:30,942 --> 00:12:32,310
You still haven't figured it out, right?

220
00:12:34,613 --> 00:12:36,415
What really happened...

221
00:12:37,182 --> 00:12:38,683
with the crime
you took the fall for back then.

222
00:12:39,718 --> 00:12:40,786
What are you talking about?

223
00:12:41,019 --> 00:12:42,621
It wasn't Chairman Choi.

224
00:12:43,822 --> 00:12:45,590
It was those two who did it.

225
00:12:46,191 --> 00:12:47,359
Those two?

226
00:13:05,277 --> 00:13:06,545
Fine, I'll explain everything.

227
00:13:06,545 --> 00:13:08,280
No, I don't need it.

228
00:13:10,248 --> 00:13:12,317
What you're thinking right now
and what you're going to say.

229
00:13:12,317 --> 00:13:13,985
I already know it all.

230
00:13:14,619 --> 00:13:15,487
Myo Jin.

231
00:13:15,787 --> 00:13:18,824
Can't we just look ahead?

232
00:13:20,992 --> 00:13:22,994
Let's just remember the fact...

233
00:13:23,729 --> 00:13:25,163
that we love each other.

234
00:13:25,697 --> 00:13:26,565
Okay?

235
00:13:27,833 --> 00:13:29,234
You said to me...

236
00:13:29,835 --> 00:13:32,137
that no matter what happens,
you'd stay by my side.

237
00:13:33,438 --> 00:13:34,439
If only the two of us were left...

238
00:13:34,439 --> 00:13:36,775
Think again about why I said that.

239
00:13:38,577 --> 00:13:40,245
The reason won't be what you think.

240
00:13:41,113 --> 00:13:43,014
It may be too hard to handle.

241
00:13:43,014 --> 00:13:43,849
No.

242
00:13:46,318 --> 00:13:47,152
I know.

243
00:13:47,586 --> 00:13:50,088
I know what you were
waiting for by my side.

244
00:13:50,655 --> 00:13:52,224
(Approached Choi Hee Su's fiancé,
Name Ryu Jun Ho)

245
00:13:52,224 --> 00:13:53,959
(Chairman Choi Young Ho supports
Ryu Jun Ho's business.)

246
00:13:53,959 --> 00:13:55,694
(Using Choi Hee Su and Ryu Jun Ho
to find out Chairman Choi's whereabouts)

247
00:13:55,694 --> 00:13:56,995
(Neither of them has noticed.)

248
00:14:00,198 --> 00:14:02,000
I looked into Chairman Choi Young Ho.

249
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:03,268
That's a relief.

250
00:14:05,103 --> 00:14:05,971
Me...

251
00:14:06,605 --> 00:14:07,472
and Hee Su.

252
00:14:08,507 --> 00:14:09,674
We were just means to an end.

253
00:14:11,410 --> 00:14:13,678
Tools for you
to get to Chairman Choi Young Ho.

254
00:14:14,279 --> 00:14:16,982
Myo Jin must be really curious
about my dad.

255
00:14:17,883 --> 00:14:19,518
She talks about him every day.

256
00:14:22,220 --> 00:14:24,022
That has nothing to do...

257
00:14:24,790 --> 00:14:25,924
with the fact that we love each other.

258
00:14:27,025 --> 00:14:27,926
Impressive.

259
00:14:29,761 --> 00:14:31,329
The way you can say that so shamelessly,

260
00:14:31,329 --> 00:14:33,699
as if you did nothing wrong.

261
00:14:36,134 --> 00:14:37,002
No!

262
00:14:38,837 --> 00:14:41,506
I know what I did wrong.

263
00:14:41,506 --> 00:14:43,075
I won't run from it.

264
00:14:43,341 --> 00:14:44,576
I'll pay any price...

265
00:14:44,576 --> 00:14:46,311
until you're fully satisfied,

266
00:14:46,311 --> 00:14:47,412
as much as it takes.

267
00:14:53,018 --> 00:14:56,221
(Seoul Namyeong Police Station)

268
00:15:00,759 --> 00:15:01,626
Sir.

269
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:03,829
The warrant for Ham Myo Jin
has been issued.

270
00:15:03,829 --> 00:15:05,097
Didn't you hear?

271
00:15:07,165 --> 00:15:08,400
Aren't you happy?

272
00:15:09,334 --> 00:15:11,036
We have solid evidence and a warrant.

273
00:15:11,269 --> 00:15:13,171
Let's say we arrest Ham Myo Jin.

274
00:15:13,672 --> 00:15:15,006
But what happens to Ryu Jun Ho?

275
00:15:16,208 --> 00:15:18,043
We still don't have
solid physical evidence.

276
00:15:18,610 --> 00:15:20,312
Yeah, that's the problem.

277
00:15:22,781 --> 00:15:23,849
That is...

278
00:15:25,350 --> 00:15:26,218
Detective Kang.

279
00:15:26,785 --> 00:15:27,686
Don't tell me...

280
00:15:28,453 --> 00:15:31,056
The hard drive
with the villa CCTV recordings...

281
00:15:31,723 --> 00:15:33,358
didn't burn up and disappear,

282
00:15:34,092 --> 00:15:35,460
but was removed beforehand.

283
00:15:36,995 --> 00:15:38,363
Removed? By whom?

284
00:15:38,363 --> 00:15:41,199
Of those four fancy people, two are dead,

285
00:15:42,034 --> 00:15:43,502
and only two are left, aren't they?

286
00:15:45,537 --> 00:15:46,371
Let's go.

287
00:15:46,738 --> 00:15:48,306
Where? Right now?

288
00:15:49,007 --> 00:15:51,343
He's watching us
like he can see the palm of his hand.

289
00:15:52,110 --> 00:15:53,712
If he thinks Ham Myo Jin is in danger,

290
00:15:54,546 --> 00:15:55,514
do you think he'll sit still?

291
00:15:56,048 --> 00:15:57,315
We don't have time. Come on!

292
00:15:57,783 --> 00:15:58,850
Sir.

293
00:16:01,753 --> 00:16:02,587
Fine.

294
00:16:04,990 --> 00:16:07,125
Before I met you,

295
00:16:08,060 --> 00:16:10,062
I'd never lived as myself.

296
00:16:11,897 --> 00:16:15,600
All that wealth and honor
the world envies...

297
00:16:17,035 --> 00:16:18,570
were given to me by those two people.

298
00:16:20,238 --> 00:16:22,107
But there was a condition.

299
00:16:25,310 --> 00:16:26,278
Obedience.

300
00:16:26,845 --> 00:16:27,846
You little punk.

301
00:16:28,547 --> 00:16:29,448
Dad.

302
00:16:34,786 --> 00:16:38,423
You should think things through
before you do anything.

303
00:16:38,924 --> 00:16:41,693
Do you want me to tell you
what's going on right now?

304
00:16:42,994 --> 00:16:43,895
I'm sorry.

305
00:16:48,734 --> 00:16:50,802
Your flight leaves at dawn tomorrow.

306
00:16:51,470 --> 00:16:53,638
Stay completely quiet...

307
00:16:54,072 --> 00:16:55,407
until I send someone.

308
00:17:04,316 --> 00:17:05,283
Good job.

309
00:17:07,853 --> 00:17:10,756
From now on too,
you're the one who protects Hee Su.

310
00:17:11,723 --> 00:17:13,992
But know your place.

311
00:17:14,860 --> 00:17:17,462
If you don't, I'll teach you.

312
00:17:31,576 --> 00:17:33,545
I wanted to get away.

313
00:17:33,545 --> 00:17:34,479
I really did.

314
00:17:37,516 --> 00:17:40,118
Even if I had to give back
everything I'd received,

315
00:17:40,385 --> 00:17:42,754
I wanted to run away from those two.

316
00:17:45,657 --> 00:17:46,758
Would that have been possible?

317
00:17:51,396 --> 00:17:52,230
Would it?

318
00:17:53,198 --> 00:17:54,800
You knew too.

319
00:17:54,800 --> 00:17:56,902
You knew, and still accepted me.

320
00:17:58,670 --> 00:17:59,504
That's right.

321
00:18:00,138 --> 00:18:02,307
Maybe, regardless of my revenge,

322
00:18:03,775 --> 00:18:06,678
I could have shared
the future you wanted...

323
00:18:08,980 --> 00:18:11,083
only if my memories hadn't returned,

324
00:18:11,717 --> 00:18:14,386
and I'd never learned the truth
until the end.

325
00:18:14,386 --> 00:18:15,187
Myo Jin.

326
00:18:15,187 --> 00:18:16,088
In this world,

327
00:18:16,088 --> 00:18:18,990
no matter how hard you try,
there are things you can never forget.

328
00:18:20,959 --> 00:18:22,461
Like my parents,

329
00:18:24,396 --> 00:18:25,797
whom you killed that day.

330
00:18:26,798 --> 00:18:28,533
No matter what I say,

331
00:18:29,668 --> 00:18:30,802
I know I can't undo that...

332
00:18:32,237 --> 00:18:34,573
or be forgiven.

333
00:18:35,140 --> 00:18:36,742
I'll spend my whole life atoning.

334
00:18:36,742 --> 00:18:38,143
Please give me a chance.

335
00:18:40,879 --> 00:18:41,747
Please.

336
00:18:43,181 --> 00:18:44,750
Don't look back.

337
00:18:44,750 --> 00:18:46,051
Let's just move forward.

338
00:18:47,886 --> 00:18:48,754
Give up.

339
00:18:50,655 --> 00:18:52,391
I'm no longer...

340
00:18:52,391 --> 00:18:54,559
the deranged patient you think I am.

341
00:18:57,295 --> 00:18:59,264
Do you really have to do this?

342
00:19:01,967 --> 00:19:03,035
Even if it means giving up...

343
00:19:06,104 --> 00:19:07,939
our entire future?

344
00:19:10,709 --> 00:19:12,544
I can't listen to this anymore.

345
00:19:12,911 --> 00:19:13,812
It's disgusting.

346
00:19:13,812 --> 00:19:15,380
Please, Myo Jin.

347
00:19:15,781 --> 00:19:16,615
Please.

348
00:19:18,850 --> 00:19:21,586
If this moment passes us by like this,

349
00:19:22,821 --> 00:19:24,756
you and I both...

350
00:19:29,795 --> 00:19:30,996
will regret it.

351
00:19:31,363 --> 00:19:33,198
You're going to pay.

352
00:19:34,566 --> 00:19:36,101
Because that recording
you heard earlier...

353
00:19:37,803 --> 00:19:39,971
will soon be heard by other people too.

354
00:20:02,694 --> 00:20:03,895
So this...

355
00:20:06,698 --> 00:20:07,999
was your idea of payback?

356
00:20:10,769 --> 00:20:11,837
Where is Ham Myo Jin?

357
00:20:11,837 --> 00:20:13,038
On the second floor.

358
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:16,641
What is this?

359
00:20:20,312 --> 00:20:21,246
Wait.

360
00:20:21,646 --> 00:20:22,514
Ham Myo Jin.

361
00:20:23,982 --> 00:20:25,684
This is her room.

362
00:20:29,020 --> 00:20:29,988
What happened?

363
00:20:30,422 --> 00:20:32,023
She was definitely here.

364
00:20:32,858 --> 00:20:33,892
Hold on.

365
00:20:34,393 --> 00:20:35,193
Damn it.

366
00:20:57,482 --> 00:20:58,550
Atibam?

367
00:20:59,885 --> 00:21:01,953
Ryu Jun Ho isn't answering either.

368
00:21:01,953 --> 00:21:04,356
When they're together,
they usually don't pick up,

369
00:21:04,356 --> 00:21:06,024
so I think they're probably together.

370
00:21:07,859 --> 00:21:09,061
First, we grab Ham Myo Jin,

371
00:21:09,828 --> 00:21:11,797
that cocky little bitch, by the throat,

372
00:21:12,631 --> 00:21:14,966
and use her to shake down
that thief Ryu Jun Ho.

373
00:21:15,534 --> 00:21:16,535
I saw that bastard Ryu Jun Ho...

374
00:21:17,836 --> 00:21:20,172
nurse Ham Myo Jin,

375
00:21:20,172 --> 00:21:22,808
and he was absolutely crazy about her.

376
00:21:22,808 --> 00:21:24,209
Of course.

377
00:21:24,943 --> 00:21:28,413
So in the end, you want to squeeze
money out of Mono Group?

378
00:21:51,770 --> 00:21:53,505
This place has a nice atmosphere.

379
00:21:54,373 --> 00:21:56,308
You really do have good instincts.

380
00:21:58,744 --> 00:22:01,012
I don't care because
it's a neighborhood nobody notices,

381
00:22:02,047 --> 00:22:03,048
but will you be all right?

382
00:22:04,916 --> 00:22:05,817
What are you talking about?

383
00:22:06,218 --> 00:22:08,987
Are you saying you plan to kill today?

384
00:22:09,521 --> 00:22:11,590
No, that's not it.

385
00:22:11,990 --> 00:22:14,793
I'm saying they'll be able to trace
Ham Myo Jin coming all the way here later.

386
00:22:15,093 --> 00:22:16,228
What do we do about that?

387
00:22:16,595 --> 00:22:18,330
Look at the cat worrying about the mouse.

388
00:22:30,142 --> 00:22:32,878
But does Ham Myo Jin know this place?

389
00:22:33,879 --> 00:22:35,080
A place this empty and out of the way?

390
00:22:35,881 --> 00:22:38,550
Somehow, right after I got out of prison,

391
00:22:39,584 --> 00:22:42,087
she came here with a knife
in less than a week.

392
00:22:42,721 --> 00:22:43,822
Look here.

393
00:22:45,190 --> 00:22:46,425
She gave me this medal.

394
00:22:47,325 --> 00:22:48,660
Damn.

395
00:22:48,960 --> 00:22:51,329
I'm telling you,
that girl is vicious as hell.

396
00:22:52,097 --> 00:22:53,398
Just wait until the job's done.

397
00:22:53,799 --> 00:22:55,767
I'll bury her nice and neat
in a sunny spot.

398
00:22:57,736 --> 00:22:58,503
What?

399
00:23:04,242 --> 00:23:05,377
Is that Ham Myo Jin's car?

400
00:23:05,777 --> 00:23:06,812
Yeah, that's right.

401
00:23:07,612 --> 00:23:09,614
- Or not?
- Who else would come but her?

402
00:23:11,116 --> 00:23:12,984
She arrived right on time.

403
00:23:12,984 --> 00:23:14,252
Okay.

404
00:23:16,755 --> 00:23:17,923
When you go there,

405
00:23:18,757 --> 00:23:20,892
the two bastards
I mentioned will be there.

406
00:23:22,194 --> 00:23:24,663
I said I'd go after finishing work
at the construction site,

407
00:23:25,330 --> 00:23:26,465
so even if a truck shows up,

408
00:23:26,932 --> 00:23:28,367
they won't avoid it.

409
00:23:28,367 --> 00:23:30,135
You want me to ram them with my car?

410
00:23:30,669 --> 00:23:31,503
Yes.

411
00:23:32,771 --> 00:23:34,473
They're quick to catch on,

412
00:23:35,273 --> 00:23:36,775
so don't let your guard down.

413
00:23:37,676 --> 00:23:38,944
End it in one strike.

414
00:23:39,611 --> 00:23:40,479
Boss.

415
00:23:40,879 --> 00:23:42,547
I'm a marksman.

416
00:23:43,148 --> 00:23:44,282
You know me.

417
00:23:44,983 --> 00:23:45,984
How many guys
have vanished without a trace...

418
00:23:45,984 --> 00:23:48,754
after I set my sights on them?

419
00:23:49,788 --> 00:23:51,957
There's one more.

420
00:23:55,360 --> 00:23:58,130
When the job's done,
come straight to the shop.

421
00:23:58,130 --> 00:23:58,964
Got it?

422
00:24:02,267 --> 00:24:03,368
- Sir.
- Yeah?

423
00:24:03,735 --> 00:24:05,337
I'll stay around the back for now,

424
00:24:05,837 --> 00:24:08,306
so you just get Ham Myo Jin
to step out of the car.

425
00:24:08,306 --> 00:24:09,174
Got it?

426
00:24:12,177 --> 00:24:13,745
Just stay here. It's fine.

427
00:24:14,212 --> 00:24:16,114
She thinks she's meeting you alone.

428
00:24:18,316 --> 00:24:20,419
I told her I'd be with a guest.

429
00:24:20,952 --> 00:24:21,753
What?

430
00:24:22,387 --> 00:24:25,057
Come to think of it,
we really do have quite a bond.

431
00:24:26,391 --> 00:24:28,326
What are you suddenly talking about?

432
00:24:28,326 --> 00:24:30,095
I've lived my whole life like a dog,

433
00:24:30,662 --> 00:24:32,798
and now I even have a friend
to go to the afterlife with.

434
00:24:33,532 --> 00:24:35,967
What a luxury this is,
right at the end of a dead-end life.

435
00:24:42,941 --> 00:24:43,842
Damn it.

436
00:24:44,910 --> 00:24:46,378
- Let go of me.
- Come here.

437
00:24:46,378 --> 00:24:47,446
What are you doing? Are you crazy?

438
00:24:52,384 --> 00:24:53,251
Let me go.

439
00:24:54,386 --> 00:24:57,189
She's a kid whose life was ruined...

440
00:24:57,189 --> 00:24:58,990
because she was stupid enough
to be fooled by you.

441
00:24:58,990 --> 00:24:59,925
And yet,

442
00:25:00,892 --> 00:25:03,462
you want me to hand her over again
to a worm like you again?

443
00:25:04,363 --> 00:25:06,064
Why are you two fighting?

444
00:25:06,064 --> 00:25:07,999
You damn lowlifes.

445
00:25:17,109 --> 00:25:19,911
If you want to die,
die alone, you son of a bitch.

446
00:25:20,112 --> 00:25:21,680
For trash like us,

447
00:25:22,314 --> 00:25:23,482
this is only right.

448
00:25:39,064 --> 00:25:40,766
Damn it.

449
00:25:41,433 --> 00:25:42,901
Are we too late here too?

450
00:25:42,901 --> 00:25:45,070
What on earth is going on?

451
00:25:45,537 --> 00:25:46,371
Sir.

452
00:25:46,872 --> 00:25:48,407
Both their phones are turned off.

453
00:25:48,907 --> 00:25:50,208
They're definitely together.

454
00:25:51,576 --> 00:25:52,711
Damn it!

455
00:26:02,554 --> 00:26:03,722
Choi Hee Su.

456
00:26:10,829 --> 00:26:12,831
(Kutmin)

457
00:26:14,099 --> 00:26:14,966
Sir.

458
00:26:15,934 --> 00:26:17,235
Isn't this an anesthetic?

459
00:26:20,939 --> 00:26:22,908
(Kutmin)

460
00:26:22,908 --> 00:26:23,842
It is.

461
00:26:24,543 --> 00:26:26,344
A kutumin-based drug...

462
00:26:27,345 --> 00:26:28,613
used for general anesthesia.

463
00:26:30,048 --> 00:26:32,818
Atibam and Kutmin.

464
00:26:33,618 --> 00:26:35,687
Ham Myo Jin and Ryu Jun Ho are together,

465
00:26:35,687 --> 00:26:36,855
so why would they need
something like that?

466
00:27:41,053 --> 00:27:42,487
I always thought...

467
00:27:48,460 --> 00:27:51,830
that the fact you'd lost
all your memories meant,

468
00:27:53,065 --> 00:27:53,899
in the end,

469
00:27:55,600 --> 00:27:57,703
that you and I...

470
00:27:59,705 --> 00:28:01,873
were destined to be the only ones left.

471
00:28:03,475 --> 00:28:05,043
That's not...

472
00:28:06,344 --> 00:28:07,446
destiny.

473
00:28:10,415 --> 00:28:12,851
It's delusion.

474
00:28:20,092 --> 00:28:21,226
Is that so?

475
00:28:23,128 --> 00:28:24,629
When we first met,

476
00:28:30,068 --> 00:28:31,036
I felt...

477
00:28:32,404 --> 00:28:34,639
that you shared the same feelings...

478
00:28:37,109 --> 00:28:37,909
as I did.

479
00:28:37,909 --> 00:28:38,744
Of course,

480
00:28:40,812 --> 00:28:43,215
it was probably all part of your plan.

481
00:28:44,950 --> 00:28:46,785
That's when I made my mistake.

482
00:28:48,754 --> 00:28:49,654
That day,

483
00:28:52,557 --> 00:28:54,793
if I hadn't said those words...

484
00:28:56,928 --> 00:29:00,866
(The day before the accident)

485
00:29:15,247 --> 00:29:16,281
Jun Ho.

486
00:29:22,254 --> 00:29:23,088
Yeah?

487
00:29:24,990 --> 00:29:26,358
You should sleep some more.

488
00:29:26,758 --> 00:29:28,326
Do you have to go to the airport already?

489
00:29:31,997 --> 00:29:33,665
I'm about to head out.

490
00:29:41,707 --> 00:29:42,674
I'm scared.

491
00:29:44,543 --> 00:29:46,344
I'm scared you'll disappear...

492
00:29:46,344 --> 00:29:47,679
while I'm in Germany.

493
00:29:49,614 --> 00:29:51,516
You said it was a conference
you couldn't miss.

494
00:29:53,085 --> 00:29:55,187
Can you make me one promise?

495
00:29:56,588 --> 00:29:57,422
What?

496
00:29:57,856 --> 00:29:59,524
That no matter what happens,

497
00:30:01,193 --> 00:30:02,627
you won't leave me.

498
00:30:08,667 --> 00:30:10,602
You're thinking
about those two people again.

499
00:30:12,738 --> 00:30:15,907
To you, they're like family.

500
00:30:15,907 --> 00:30:16,742
And to me...

501
00:30:16,742 --> 00:30:17,976
Just tell me that.

502
00:30:19,010 --> 00:30:20,979
That no matter what happens,

503
00:30:23,048 --> 00:30:24,483
you won't leave me.

504
00:30:29,688 --> 00:30:31,757
Whenever I ask you something like this,

505
00:30:32,724 --> 00:30:34,025
you're always the same.

506
00:30:35,026 --> 00:30:37,796
I still haven't heard the answer I want.

507
00:30:38,263 --> 00:30:39,998
I'm right here beside you.

508
00:30:41,133 --> 00:30:42,367
I'm not going anywhere.

509
00:30:42,567 --> 00:30:43,602
I still...

510
00:30:46,138 --> 00:30:47,406
haven't heard you say...

511
00:30:47,973 --> 00:30:49,708
you love me even once.

512
00:30:50,509 --> 00:30:51,476
If...

513
00:30:53,879 --> 00:30:57,516
only the two of us were left...

514
00:31:04,990 --> 00:31:06,058
That will happen.

515
00:31:06,892 --> 00:31:07,793
I'm sure of it.

516
00:31:09,995 --> 00:31:10,862
Hee Su.

517
00:31:13,065 --> 00:31:14,366
Tomorrow is her birthday.

518
00:31:16,735 --> 00:31:19,905
When it's just the two of us,
I want us to talk about us.

519
00:31:20,806 --> 00:31:21,606
But...

520
00:31:21,606 --> 00:31:23,942
Chairman Choi returned
to Korea last night.

521
00:31:24,676 --> 00:31:26,278
The two of them will be together now.

522
00:31:27,379 --> 00:31:28,413
Don't worry.

523
00:31:29,881 --> 00:31:30,882
I see.

524
00:32:04,483 --> 00:32:06,251
- Enjoy your meal.
- Thank you.

525
00:32:10,055 --> 00:32:10,889
Myo Jin.

526
00:32:11,990 --> 00:32:12,758
Sorry.

527
00:32:21,199 --> 00:32:23,168
Chairman Choi Young Ho is back in Korea.

528
00:32:24,102 --> 00:32:24,936
Are you sure?

529
00:32:26,004 --> 00:32:27,739
Tomorrow is Hee Su's birthday,

530
00:32:27,739 --> 00:32:29,107
and he couldn't be with her last year,

531
00:32:29,107 --> 00:32:30,876
so he said he would
definitely come this year.

532
00:32:31,410 --> 00:32:33,111
Ryu Jun Ho said the same thing.

533
00:32:33,345 --> 00:32:34,513
It should be right.

534
00:32:34,513 --> 00:32:35,714
The chance has come.

535
00:32:35,714 --> 00:32:37,549
Ryu Jun Ho went to Germany this morning...

536
00:32:37,549 --> 00:32:38,950
for the conference.

537
00:32:39,785 --> 00:32:42,054
At the Jebu-do villa right now,
there should only be...

538
00:32:42,054 --> 00:32:43,255
Choi Young Ho and Choi Hee Su.

539
00:32:43,722 --> 00:32:45,190
This is a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

540
00:32:46,425 --> 00:32:47,759
How can I help?

541
00:32:53,765 --> 00:32:54,599
No.

542
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:57,102
From here on, I'll handle it myself.

543
00:32:57,335 --> 00:32:58,737
Don't rush.

544
00:32:59,404 --> 00:33:00,839
They're not easy people.

545
00:33:02,507 --> 00:33:03,809
I'm ready.

546
00:33:04,810 --> 00:33:05,877
If I can kill...

547
00:33:06,878 --> 00:33:09,414
Choi Young Ho with my own hands,

548
00:33:10,282 --> 00:33:11,950
I don't care what happens to me.

549
00:33:12,718 --> 00:33:15,053
Don't rush. Take it slow.

550
00:33:16,288 --> 00:33:17,956
You said that to me once.

551
00:33:17,956 --> 00:33:18,924
Don't forget it.

552
00:33:32,237 --> 00:33:33,138
Hello?

553
00:33:33,438 --> 00:33:34,339
It's me.

554
00:33:35,674 --> 00:33:36,742
Jun Ho?

555
00:33:36,742 --> 00:33:37,576
Yeah.

556
00:33:38,610 --> 00:33:40,011
Have you already arrived?

557
00:33:40,278 --> 00:33:42,848
No. Chief Kim went to Germany in my place.

558
00:33:44,783 --> 00:33:47,052
How can someone else
attend the conference for you?

559
00:33:47,619 --> 00:33:49,121
I explained it well, so it's fine.

560
00:33:50,288 --> 00:33:52,491
I came to Japan for something urgent.

561
00:33:55,293 --> 00:33:57,396
I'll take care of some work and meet you,
even if it's late tonight.

562
00:33:57,763 --> 00:34:00,198
Around what time today?

563
00:34:00,832 --> 00:34:01,800
Late.

564
00:34:03,368 --> 00:34:04,936
I'll call you back on this number.

565
00:34:17,949 --> 00:34:20,852
The phone you have called is turned off.
After the beep...

566
00:34:31,997 --> 00:34:35,834
(The day of the accident)

567
00:35:43,935 --> 00:35:46,738
(LPG)

568
00:37:13,492 --> 00:37:14,659
Look who's here.

569
00:37:15,560 --> 00:37:16,495
Ham Myo Jin.

570
00:37:17,429 --> 00:37:19,064
You came all the way here?

571
00:37:20,365 --> 00:37:21,333
It's been a while.

572
00:37:37,949 --> 00:37:40,085
I know you didn't come
because you missed me.

573
00:37:41,119 --> 00:37:41,987
So why?

574
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:44,056
Did you suddenly have something to ask?

575
00:37:49,094 --> 00:37:51,797
Or did you come to laugh at me?

576
00:37:52,097 --> 00:37:53,699
Sorry, but neither.

577
00:37:54,966 --> 00:37:56,768
I have nothing left to say to you.

578
00:37:56,768 --> 00:37:57,536
Really?

579
00:37:58,704 --> 00:37:59,905
I see.

580
00:38:04,543 --> 00:38:06,211
Are you trying to beat me to it?

581
00:38:06,945 --> 00:38:09,715
Do you think I still don't know
about you and Ryu Jun Ho?

582
00:38:10,348 --> 00:38:11,717
Think whatever you want.

583
00:38:13,351 --> 00:38:15,420
I'm not interested
in the two of you anymore.

584
00:38:16,855 --> 00:38:18,724
When did you grow up so much?

585
00:38:19,658 --> 00:38:20,892
My little Myo Jin.

586
00:38:24,496 --> 00:38:25,697
I'm not good at this kind of thing.

587
00:38:25,697 --> 00:38:27,399
Come on, pose for me.

588
00:38:27,966 --> 00:38:29,735
You saw what I did.

589
00:38:31,536 --> 00:38:32,637
They do stuff like this.

590
00:38:34,740 --> 00:38:36,108
Should I say...

591
00:38:36,742 --> 00:38:37,943
what you want to say first?

592
00:38:39,478 --> 00:38:41,747
If you like him that much, just take him.

593
00:38:43,081 --> 00:38:44,282
I'm sick of him now.

594
00:38:47,119 --> 00:38:48,687
I did think about...

595
00:38:49,688 --> 00:38:52,124
what I should do with the two of you.

596
00:38:54,726 --> 00:38:56,395
Should I let you two go...

597
00:38:57,195 --> 00:38:59,131
or keep you two tied down?

598
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:03,902
I'm the one who always decides.

599
00:39:04,836 --> 00:39:06,505
You should know that much by now.

600
00:39:10,876 --> 00:39:11,843
Come on.

601
00:39:11,843 --> 00:39:13,612
Make a heart.

602
00:39:14,679 --> 00:39:16,081
Okay, act handsome.

603
00:39:16,081 --> 00:39:17,082
Act cool.

604
00:39:19,651 --> 00:39:21,019
You're so funny.

605
00:39:21,019 --> 00:39:22,587
Ryu Jun Ho, you're handsome.

606
00:39:25,457 --> 00:39:27,059
Do you know what my wish is?

607
00:39:27,059 --> 00:39:29,061
Come on, I want to take a picture.

608
00:39:29,061 --> 00:39:30,562
To go back to that day...

609
00:39:30,562 --> 00:39:31,329
Look here.

610
00:39:31,329 --> 00:39:33,198
and start everything over again,

611
00:39:33,965 --> 00:39:35,167
from the very beginning.

612
00:39:37,869 --> 00:39:38,937
Ryu Jun Ho...

613
00:39:41,440 --> 00:39:43,508
will never escape me
for the rest of his life.

614
00:39:46,578 --> 00:39:48,213
Without my permission,

615
00:39:48,513 --> 00:39:49,715
the two of you can't do anything.

616
00:39:52,718 --> 00:39:53,618
Do you know...

617
00:39:55,320 --> 00:39:57,089
what happened that day?

618
00:39:57,923 --> 00:39:59,524
The weather is so nice.

619
00:39:59,524 --> 00:40:00,525
Beautiful.

620
00:40:02,027 --> 00:40:03,528
Smile.

621
00:40:03,528 --> 00:40:04,529
I said smile.

622
00:40:06,732 --> 00:40:07,666
What?

623
00:40:08,300 --> 00:40:09,568
Why are you making that face?

624
00:40:10,202 --> 00:40:12,337
Anyone would think
you had some terminal illness.

625
00:40:18,510 --> 00:40:20,245
Even after seeing this,
does it still not feel real?

626
00:40:21,113 --> 00:40:23,448
We're really going to America now.

627
00:40:23,448 --> 00:40:25,050
You to Brown, me to RISD.

628
00:40:25,317 --> 00:40:26,251
Aren't you happy?

629
00:40:30,622 --> 00:40:32,357
Are you seriously
going to keep acting like this?

630
00:40:32,624 --> 00:40:34,126
Why are you so serious?

631
00:40:35,694 --> 00:40:38,130
I feel like I'm going abroad to study
by begging for it.

632
00:40:39,197 --> 00:40:40,999
Going this far to make it happen
just feels wrong.

633
00:40:40,999 --> 00:40:41,867
You fool.

634
00:40:42,701 --> 00:40:44,970
I told you I already talked to my dad.

635
00:40:44,970 --> 00:40:46,038
So what?

636
00:40:46,038 --> 00:40:48,106
Tuition and living expenses
are too much money.

637
00:40:48,573 --> 00:40:50,976
It'll keep costing this much for years.

638
00:40:50,976 --> 00:40:52,811
How can I owe him all of it?

639
00:40:52,811 --> 00:40:54,079
Get a part-time job there.

640
00:40:55,180 --> 00:40:57,282
Study hard and get a scholarship too.

641
00:40:57,716 --> 00:40:59,317
That's all. What are you worried about?

642
00:41:00,252 --> 00:41:02,220
I already did the math.

643
00:41:02,921 --> 00:41:05,290
It'll only be enough for me
to buy the books I want to read.

644
00:41:09,327 --> 00:41:10,162
You fool.

645
00:41:11,196 --> 00:41:12,397
Are you really going to do that?

646
00:41:13,131 --> 00:41:15,333
Do you think I'd just let you
struggle like that?

647
00:41:18,503 --> 00:41:19,971
Dad said so.

648
00:41:20,605 --> 00:41:22,074
You can pay him back later
once you succeed.

649
00:41:22,541 --> 00:41:23,909
Then it's fine.

650
00:41:23,909 --> 00:41:25,343
Even so...

651
00:41:25,343 --> 00:41:26,478
Be quiet.

652
00:41:27,679 --> 00:41:28,880
That means you should treat me well.

653
00:41:30,348 --> 00:41:31,216
Otherwise...

654
00:41:32,617 --> 00:41:33,618
Otherwise?

655
00:41:34,052 --> 00:41:36,121
You can go be an idiot and join the army.

656
00:41:40,058 --> 00:41:41,526
You'd better be good to me.

657
00:41:50,502 --> 00:41:51,370
Hey.

658
00:41:51,370 --> 00:41:52,804
Pull over, now.

659
00:41:53,171 --> 00:41:55,440
We drank. You're drunk right now.

660
00:41:55,741 --> 00:41:56,608
I don't want to.

661
00:41:56,875 --> 00:41:58,310
There's no one around.
What's the big deal?

662
00:41:58,510 --> 00:41:59,811
It's dangerous. Pull over.

663
00:41:59,811 --> 00:42:00,779
Stop the car!

664
00:42:01,146 --> 00:42:03,115
Why are you always so serious?

665
00:42:03,482 --> 00:42:05,250
You won't let me do anything fun.

666
00:42:05,250 --> 00:42:06,818
I'm not listening to you anymore.

667
00:42:09,488 --> 00:42:10,555
Stop acting crazy.

668
00:42:10,555 --> 00:42:11,790
Stop right now!

669
00:42:12,057 --> 00:42:12,958
No.

670
00:42:13,225 --> 00:42:15,260
Who would be out here
in this backwater place?

671
00:42:15,260 --> 00:42:16,128
Let go.

672
00:42:16,862 --> 00:42:17,863
It's my choice.

673
00:42:19,798 --> 00:42:21,033
Please, stop it.

674
00:42:24,069 --> 00:42:25,504
The cherry blossoms are so beautiful.

675
00:42:28,940 --> 00:42:29,908
No!

676
00:42:42,187 --> 00:42:44,022
What if she finds out it died?

677
00:42:45,290 --> 00:42:46,658
Myo Jin...

678
00:42:47,559 --> 00:42:49,561
will cry her eyes out.

679
00:42:50,195 --> 00:42:52,431
I'm so upset.

680
00:42:55,500 --> 00:42:58,103
What are you going to do
about the crack in your arm?

681
00:42:58,303 --> 00:43:00,439
Forget it. It's nothing.

682
00:43:00,672 --> 00:43:02,874
What do you mean, nothing?

683
00:43:02,874 --> 00:43:04,242
I was really shocked.

684
00:43:05,043 --> 00:43:07,979
In this day and age,
how can young people still drive drunk?

685
00:43:09,481 --> 00:43:10,415
So?

686
00:43:11,550 --> 00:43:12,784
What did those kids say?

687
00:43:14,953 --> 00:43:16,855
They brought up money first.

688
00:43:16,855 --> 00:43:18,623
They said they'd pay whatever I asked,

689
00:43:18,623 --> 00:43:20,392
as long as I didn't report them.

690
00:43:22,594 --> 00:43:26,631
Young kids like that, with that mindset...

691
00:43:28,467 --> 00:43:30,068
Then what about our dog?

692
00:43:31,103 --> 00:43:33,538
What did they say about killing our dog?

693
00:43:34,840 --> 00:43:36,742
If they don't even care
that a person got hurt,

694
00:43:36,742 --> 00:43:38,877
do you think they care about a mere dog?

695
00:43:39,711 --> 00:43:41,413
What nasty little brats.

696
00:43:42,147 --> 00:43:43,682
Before they cause an even bigger accident,

697
00:43:43,682 --> 00:43:45,550
shouldn't someone teach them a lesson?

698
00:43:45,550 --> 00:43:46,418
Yes.

699
00:43:46,985 --> 00:43:49,287
I told them
I was reporting them to the police,

700
00:43:49,287 --> 00:43:51,356
so they'd better be ready.

701
00:43:51,690 --> 00:43:54,059
I said they should go to jail
and learn their lesson.

702
00:43:54,593 --> 00:43:56,795
I took photos of everything on my phone.

703
00:44:07,205 --> 00:44:10,142
They say drunk-driving laws
are really strict these days.

704
00:44:11,576 --> 00:44:13,011
Isn't that a bit too far?

705
00:44:14,446 --> 00:44:17,249
Ruining young kids' futures is too...

706
00:44:20,852 --> 00:44:22,554
I know.

707
00:44:22,554 --> 00:44:23,889
I won't call the police.

708
00:44:24,222 --> 00:44:25,924
I didn't even report them.

709
00:44:27,492 --> 00:44:29,895
But those kids...

710
00:45:13,071 --> 00:45:13,972
Hee Su.

711
00:45:14,239 --> 00:45:15,540
It's all because of you.

712
00:45:15,540 --> 00:45:16,641
Get out of my sight.

713
00:45:16,641 --> 00:45:18,510
Disappear from my sight.

714
00:45:18,510 --> 00:45:19,611
You and I...

715
00:45:19,945 --> 00:45:21,413
were driving drunk without licenses.

716
00:45:21,747 --> 00:45:23,615
Forget studying in America. It's all over.

717
00:45:24,082 --> 00:45:25,951
My life is over!

718
00:45:31,490 --> 00:45:32,824
Dad is going to kill me.

719
00:45:33,325 --> 00:45:34,359
Hey.

720
00:45:34,359 --> 00:45:35,727
What are you going to tell my dad?

721
00:45:38,864 --> 00:45:40,832
What am I supposed to do
if you just do nothing like that?

722
00:45:41,199 --> 00:45:42,868
Are you not thinking at all right now?

723
00:45:42,868 --> 00:45:44,202
Are you insane?

724
00:45:44,436 --> 00:45:46,438
What about your promise to my dad?

725
00:45:46,938 --> 00:45:49,908
You did this to me,
and you have nothing to say?

726
00:45:50,375 --> 00:45:51,676
I'll figure something out.

727
00:45:52,511 --> 00:45:53,345
Shut up.

728
00:45:55,280 --> 00:45:56,681
He filmed everything...

729
00:45:57,182 --> 00:45:58,683
and took the liquor bottles
with our fingerprints on them...

730
00:45:58,683 --> 00:45:59,951
to hand over to the police.

731
00:46:00,352 --> 00:46:01,820
I refused to go to the police station,

732
00:46:01,820 --> 00:46:03,422
so we only barely avoided
being dragged there.

733
00:46:03,422 --> 00:46:04,322
Hey.

734
00:46:04,322 --> 00:46:06,425
Why the hell did you admit that I drank?

735
00:46:07,592 --> 00:46:08,393
Why?

736
00:46:08,894 --> 00:46:10,262
After you did
every stupid thing you could,

737
00:46:10,262 --> 00:46:12,164
what are you going to do now?

738
00:46:32,651 --> 00:46:33,585
I know.

739
00:46:37,122 --> 00:46:39,124
This is something I should handle.

740
00:46:41,259 --> 00:46:43,562
I promised your father
I'd take care of you.

741
00:46:47,866 --> 00:46:49,000
I'll handle it myself.

742
00:46:51,870 --> 00:46:53,472
That's what I'm here for.

743
00:46:58,076 --> 00:46:59,511
If it's for you, I should do it.

744
00:47:01,813 --> 00:47:02,948
That's how it should be.

745
00:47:13,759 --> 00:47:15,627
It was such a perfect day.

746
00:47:17,863 --> 00:47:19,664
That day was my birthday,

747
00:47:20,065 --> 00:47:20,966
and the day before,

748
00:47:22,768 --> 00:47:24,669
the acceptance letters came from America,

749
00:47:24,970 --> 00:47:26,271
for both of us.

750
00:47:44,756 --> 00:47:45,590
Hello?

751
00:48:10,582 --> 00:48:11,516
What should I do?

752
00:48:13,685 --> 00:48:14,686
Was it...

753
00:48:16,755 --> 00:48:17,889
you two?

754
00:48:20,659 --> 00:48:21,493
What?

755
00:48:22,661 --> 00:48:24,196
Did Ryu Jun Ho tell you?

756
00:48:25,430 --> 00:48:26,298
Tell me.

757
00:48:27,999 --> 00:48:29,000
Was it you two?

758
00:48:29,000 --> 00:48:30,435
Did he tell you that?

759
00:48:32,704 --> 00:48:34,306
That crazy bastard.

760
00:48:36,341 --> 00:48:37,909
The one who set the fire was Ryu Jun Ho.

761
00:48:38,543 --> 00:48:40,579
Ryu Jun Ho killed those people.

762
00:48:44,116 --> 00:48:45,016
Why?

763
00:48:46,284 --> 00:48:47,219
For what reason?

764
00:48:47,219 --> 00:48:48,587
Are you really asking me that?

765
00:48:48,587 --> 00:48:50,021
Imagine if this got out.

766
00:48:50,021 --> 00:48:51,656
People would all blame me.

767
00:48:52,424 --> 00:48:54,493
They wouldn't even know
what really happened,

768
00:48:54,493 --> 00:48:56,661
but they'd all go crazy
trying to tear me apart.

769
00:49:00,265 --> 00:49:02,267
It wasn't something
that had to get that big.

770
00:49:05,037 --> 00:49:06,538
Yes, we caused the accident,

771
00:49:07,072 --> 00:49:08,640
but we admitted our mistake...

772
00:49:09,007 --> 00:49:12,144
and said we'd compensate him fully,
as much as he wanted.

773
00:49:12,144 --> 00:49:14,546
But he kept threatening
to put us in prison.

774
00:49:15,514 --> 00:49:16,581
Is that...

775
00:49:19,017 --> 00:49:20,886
the reason...

776
00:49:22,854 --> 00:49:23,789
you killed people?

777
00:49:26,324 --> 00:49:28,226
They weren't people...

778
00:49:30,562 --> 00:49:31,963
who deserved...

779
00:49:32,998 --> 00:49:33,832
to die like that.

780
00:49:50,515 --> 00:49:51,516
I told you.

781
00:49:53,585 --> 00:49:54,720
From that moment on,

782
00:49:57,255 --> 00:49:59,091
I had a reason it had to be that way.

783
00:50:00,726 --> 00:50:02,027
Now you understand too, don't you?

784
00:50:03,395 --> 00:50:04,363
How I felt.

785
00:50:05,831 --> 00:50:07,165
Do you understand my pain?

786
00:50:07,165 --> 00:50:08,266
That was your reason...

787
00:50:09,868 --> 00:50:11,336
for killing those people?

788
00:50:11,336 --> 00:50:12,571
I told you.

789
00:50:12,838 --> 00:50:15,374
Back then, we got acceptance letters
from the best universities in America.

790
00:50:15,374 --> 00:50:16,274
Can that...

791
00:50:18,176 --> 00:50:20,379
be a reason to kill people?

792
00:50:25,317 --> 00:50:27,252
People with nothing to lose...

793
00:50:28,086 --> 00:50:30,589
all think like you, of course.

794
00:50:31,957 --> 00:50:32,824
What?

795
00:50:34,960 --> 00:50:35,727
You.

796
00:50:36,228 --> 00:50:38,597
When you first came to my exhibition
and saw my paintings, you cried.

797
00:50:39,431 --> 00:50:40,532
You said it yourself...

798
00:50:41,366 --> 00:50:43,201
that you could feel
my sorrow inside my paintings.

799
00:50:43,568 --> 00:50:44,469
My passion,

800
00:50:45,103 --> 00:50:47,372
my talent, all of it, so vividly.

801
00:50:47,939 --> 00:50:49,941
You said that you'd never felt
anything like it before.

802
00:50:51,343 --> 00:50:52,577
You're insane.

803
00:50:53,945 --> 00:50:56,248
If those people had ruined me back then,

804
00:51:02,587 --> 00:51:03,755
my paintings...

805
00:51:06,158 --> 00:51:07,759
wouldn't exist in the world now.

806
00:51:11,496 --> 00:51:12,998
Can you even imagine that?

807
00:51:19,838 --> 00:51:20,772
Hey.

808
00:51:21,006 --> 00:51:23,709
Do you know
what people with nothing to lose...

809
00:51:25,277 --> 00:51:27,045
are capable of?

810
00:51:31,717 --> 00:51:32,751
They only wait for their chance.

811
00:51:33,351 --> 00:51:35,921
They wait to find fault
with people who have money,

812
00:51:36,254 --> 00:51:38,190
and when they get the chance,
they pounce and rip them apart.

813
00:51:38,190 --> 00:51:39,057
Like animals.

814
00:51:39,991 --> 00:51:41,760
That's what happened to us that day.

815
00:51:42,661 --> 00:51:44,796
There is no one in this world
who has nothing to lose.

816
00:51:45,764 --> 00:51:48,400
Because those people were
someone's father and someone's mother too.

817
00:53:15,387 --> 00:53:16,722
Honey.

818
00:53:17,856 --> 00:53:19,558
Honey, what do we do?

819
00:53:19,558 --> 00:53:20,926
It's a fire. Wait.

820
00:53:22,461 --> 00:53:23,362
Honey.

821
00:53:23,362 --> 00:53:24,896
Wait a second.

822
00:53:30,302 --> 00:53:31,136
No.

823
00:53:37,275 --> 00:53:38,110
Mom.

824
00:53:38,643 --> 00:53:40,011
Mom, Dad.

825
00:53:43,248 --> 00:53:45,584
- Myo Jin.
- Mom.

826
00:53:45,584 --> 00:53:46,485
Myo Jin.

827
00:53:46,485 --> 00:53:47,419
Mom.

828
00:53:48,220 --> 00:53:49,087
Myo Jin.

829
00:53:51,857 --> 00:53:52,891
Honey.

830
00:53:53,558 --> 00:53:55,327
Mom.

831
00:53:56,595 --> 00:53:57,462
Mom.

832
00:53:59,664 --> 00:54:01,099
Mom, no.

833
00:54:01,099 --> 00:54:02,501
No.

834
00:54:03,769 --> 00:54:04,970
No, Mom.

835
00:54:04,970 --> 00:54:06,671
Myo Jin, get out quickly.

836
00:54:06,671 --> 00:54:09,107
I'll get your mom out. Go.

837
00:54:09,107 --> 00:54:10,242
- Go.
- Hurry, go.

838
00:54:10,242 --> 00:54:12,010
Go, Myo Jin.

839
00:54:12,010 --> 00:54:13,178
No.

840
00:54:13,178 --> 00:54:15,380
I can't go.

841
00:54:15,380 --> 00:54:17,215
Go, Myo Jin.

842
00:54:17,215 --> 00:54:18,683
No.

843
00:54:23,088 --> 00:54:24,589
What is happening?

844
00:54:26,792 --> 00:54:27,793
Mom, Dad.

845
00:54:27,793 --> 00:54:29,161
Mom, Dad, no.

846
00:54:29,161 --> 00:54:30,929
Mom, Dad.

847
00:54:31,396 --> 00:54:33,098
Why won't this work? Get up.

848
00:54:33,098 --> 00:54:34,132
Dad, no.

849
00:54:34,132 --> 00:54:35,133
No.

850
00:54:35,133 --> 00:54:36,702
No, Mom.

851
00:54:36,702 --> 00:54:37,703
Dad.

852
00:54:39,571 --> 00:54:40,839
Myo Jin.

853
00:54:40,839 --> 00:54:42,407
Myo Jin!

854
00:54:45,811 --> 00:54:46,778
Myo Jin.

855
00:54:47,479 --> 00:54:48,747
If you go in there, you'll die.

856
00:54:48,747 --> 00:54:50,549
- Dad.
- You'll die too.

857
00:54:50,549 --> 00:54:52,551
Mom, Dad.

858
00:54:54,019 --> 00:54:55,087
Dad.

859
00:55:01,026 --> 00:55:01,993
No.

860
00:55:02,227 --> 00:55:03,261
No.

861
00:55:03,595 --> 00:55:04,963
No.

862
00:55:04,963 --> 00:55:05,964
No!

863
00:55:42,434 --> 00:55:47,005
(REVERSE)

864
00:55:47,305 --> 00:55:49,241
Choi Hee Su and Ryu Jun Ho.

865
00:55:49,241 --> 00:55:50,876
I'm sure it isn't a coincidence.

866
00:55:50,876 --> 00:55:53,445
Because there's no such thing
as revenge that only gives back...

867
00:55:53,445 --> 00:55:54,780
what was done to you.

868
00:55:54,780 --> 00:55:56,448
Should I give that present to you?

869
00:55:56,782 --> 00:55:59,351
You have to remember.

870
00:55:59,951 --> 00:56:01,620
Over one stupid memory?

871
00:56:01,620 --> 00:56:03,855
It's already over and gone.

872
00:56:03,855 --> 00:56:06,158
You went all the way to the villa
to save Choi Hee Su...

873
00:56:06,458 --> 00:56:08,026
and almost lost your life.

874
00:56:08,360 --> 00:56:11,096
But my feelings remembered you,

875
00:56:11,396 --> 00:56:13,331
and they showed me what I had to do.

876
00:56:14,199 --> 00:56:16,201
